Preconditions:
- The length of the input array `nums` is at least 3.
- The elements in the input array `nums` are integers.
- The elements in the input array `nums` are within the range of 1 to 10^9.

Postconditions:
- The output is an integer representing the minimum number of elements to remove to make `nums` a mountain array.
- The output is non-negative.
- The output is the smallest possible number of elements to remove.
- The input array `nums` is not modified.
- The input array `nums` remains the same after the method is executed.
- The input array `nums` is a mountain array after the method is executed.